      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, that is a perfect example of what an indemnification clause can cover. If you use unlicensed material and the agency gets sued, the clause likely requires you to defend them and cover their resulting costs, including legal fees and any settlement. This is how the clause shifts the risk of your mistakes onto you. It's a very common liability shield they want to have in place.",
      "source": "target",
